1
00:00:39,640 --> 00:00:42,450
Drop, drop,

2
00:00:42,480 --> 00:00:44,640
drop the handkerchief.

3
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:51,500
Gently place it behind a friend.

4
00:00:51,710 --> 00:00:55,840
Don't say a word, not even a peep.

5
00:00:56,280 --> 00:00:59,730
Hurry, run and catch him!

6
00:00:59,840 --> 00:01:05,150
Hurry, run and catch him!

7
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:08,660
If someone's coming for me...

8
00:01:09,230 --> 00:01:10,880
I'm coming for them too.

9
00:01:12,230 --> 00:01:13,289
I'll drag them out.

10
00:01:14,430 --> 00:01:15,760
We'll go down together.

11
00:02:44,570 --> 00:02:48,920
[THE GUILTY]

12
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:56,250
[Episode 1]

13
00:02:58,030 --> 00:03:03,310
[2010]

14
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:08,870
You're free now.

15
00:03:08,870 --> 00:03:10,240
Don't ever come back.

16
00:03:13,120 --> 00:03:16,290
[Nanping City Prison]

17
00:04:03,790 --> 00:04:06,410
[Nanping]

18
00:04:25,950 --> 00:04:26,510
Hello,

19
00:04:26,630 --> 00:04:27,630
Mr. Li.

20
00:04:31,030 --> 00:04:32,030
Mr. Li,

21
00:04:32,070 --> 00:04:33,730
we all have to wait for her?

22
00:04:33,760 --> 00:04:35,240
Who does she think she is?

23
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:37,360
Believe it or not, if she
holds my son back from the hospital

24
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:38,670
and he ends up with a scar,

25
00:04:38,670 --> 00:04:41,400
even her entire fortune
won’t cover the damages!

26
00:04:42,840 --> 00:04:43,650
Shanshan.

27
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:46,020
Come here. Take a seat.

28
00:04:47,870 --> 00:04:48,750
Are you hurt?

29
00:04:50,630 --> 00:04:52,240
Tell Mom what happened.

30
00:04:52,870 --> 00:04:55,990
In April, no one has a moment to spare.

31
00:04:56,020 --> 00:04:59,690
In April, no one has a moment to spare.

32
00:04:59,920 --> 00:05:02,920
Silkworm work done,
and they plant the rice fields new.

33
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:06,370
Silkworm work done,
and they plant the rice fields new.

34
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:08,560
It tells the view of April
in the countryside.

35
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:10,600
These two sentences are the settings.

36
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:12,400
What are you doing? Don't fight.

37
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:15,920
It's okay.

38
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:18,040
Mr. Li, make them pay whatever is owed

39
00:05:18,040 --> 00:05:19,600
and expel whoever needs to be expelled.

40
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:21,680
If the school
doesn't give me an explanation for this,

41
00:05:21,680 --> 00:05:22,880
I'm not done with you.

42
00:05:23,310 --> 00:05:24,240
Call the police.

43
00:05:25,630 --> 00:05:26,560
Call the police?

44
00:05:26,630 --> 00:05:28,890
Your son sexually harassed my daughter.

45
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:30,720
My daughter acted in self-defense.

46
00:05:30,720 --> 00:05:31,650
Call the police,

47
00:05:31,870 --> 00:05:33,130
and let them handle it.

48
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:34,560
What nonsense are you talking about?

49
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:35,920
How could you believe
whatever your girl said?

50
00:05:35,920 --> 00:05:37,120
Do you have any proof?

51
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:39,240
Aren't there cameras in the classroom?

52
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:39,940
Pull up the surveillance footage.

53
00:05:39,940 --> 00:05:40,270
[June 5, 2010]

54
00:05:40,270 --> 00:05:44,680
Silkworm work done,
and they plant the rice fields new.

55
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:53,520
Does pulling a zipper
count as sexual harassment?

56
00:05:58,800 --> 00:05:59,510
Shanshan's mom,

57
00:05:59,510 --> 00:06:00,510
isn't this a bit too much?

58
00:06:00,510 --> 00:06:01,630
What are you doing?

59
00:06:02,510 --> 00:06:04,390
How can you compare adults and children?

60
00:06:04,390 --> 00:06:05,360
He's only ten.

61
00:06:05,360 --> 00:06:06,240
What does he know?

62
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:07,500
It was just horseplay!

63
00:06:08,020 --> 00:06:09,310
He doesn't know a thing.

64
00:06:09,310 --> 00:06:10,510
But my daughter does.

65
00:06:11,720 --> 00:06:13,720
No one's gonna call the police, huh?

66
00:06:17,310 --> 00:06:18,270
Come on.

67
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:19,560
Come on.

68
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:20,760
Forget it, forget it.

69
00:06:20,890 --> 00:06:22,550
We won't pursue this anymore.

70
00:06:24,190 --> 00:06:25,120
But I will.

71
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:30,800
It's just a trivial little thing.

72
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:32,750
Just say it, what do you want?

73
00:06:33,190 --> 00:06:33,920
An apology.

74
00:06:39,070 --> 00:06:39,680
Go on.

75
00:06:40,630 --> 00:06:41,820
My dad's a leader.

76
00:06:42,070 --> 00:06:43,220
She's nobody.

77
00:06:43,610 --> 00:06:45,270
Why should I apologize to her?

78
00:06:46,120 --> 00:06:48,360
Fine, don't apologize then.

79
00:06:49,190 --> 00:06:50,510
Let's wait for the police.

80
00:06:50,510 --> 00:06:51,390
We'll see how long your "leader" dad

81
00:06:51,390 --> 00:06:52,560
can shield you.

82
00:06:53,390 --> 00:06:55,250
Did you hear that? Apologize now!

83
00:06:55,390 --> 00:06:56,120
Hurry up.

84
00:06:57,060 --> 00:06:59,090
You promised to buy me McDonald's.

85
00:07:00,190 --> 00:07:00,800
I'm sorry.

86
00:07:02,100 --> 00:07:03,100
Apologize to her.

87
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:12,390
I'm sorry.

88
00:07:19,870 --> 00:07:21,070
Sorry, Mom.

89
00:07:21,540 --> 00:07:23,600
I shouldn't have gotten into a fight.

90
00:07:24,120 --> 00:07:26,150
And got you into arguing with them.

91
00:07:26,390 --> 00:07:27,860
You did nothing wrong.

92
00:07:28,310 --> 00:07:29,270
Remember,

93
00:07:29,270 --> 00:07:31,470
if anyone bullies you, fight back hard.

94
00:07:32,360 --> 00:07:33,950
I thought you'd scold me.

95
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:35,800
Why would I scold you?

96
00:07:36,870 --> 00:07:39,240
I will always protect you.

97
00:07:39,750 --> 00:07:40,810
Do you understand?

98
00:07:40,870 --> 00:07:41,190
Yes.

99
00:07:41,430 --> 00:07:41,750
OK.

100
00:07:42,430 --> 00:07:43,870
Good girl. Be careful.

101
00:08:22,070 --> 00:08:23,160
Ming.

102
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:25,560
You always say
we're a financial services firm.

103
00:08:25,560 --> 00:08:26,910
No violent collections.

104
00:08:26,910 --> 00:08:28,640
We must collect debts legally.

105
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:29,680
If this keeps up,

106
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:31,380
the guys won't make rent.

107
00:08:32,429 --> 00:08:35,000
When the money
from Hu Liang's enforcement comes in,

108
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:36,870
split my share among the guys.

109
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:39,299
Ming, that's not what I meant.

110
00:08:39,299 --> 00:08:40,630
Don't get me wrong.

111
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:42,549
I mean...

112
00:08:43,080 --> 00:08:43,750
Hello?

113
00:08:45,120 --> 00:08:45,870
Where?

114
00:08:45,890 --> 00:08:47,120
Where is he?

115
00:08:47,970 --> 00:08:48,970
Got it.

116
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:50,870
Ming.

117
00:08:50,930 --> 00:08:53,770
We found Ma Derong's address.

118
00:08:54,630 --> 00:08:55,320
Where is it?

119
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:56,320
Beishan Village.

120
00:09:02,990 --> 00:09:03,850
See you around.

121
00:09:23,370 --> 00:09:26,500
Ma Derong has been hiding here
since he got out of prison.

122
00:09:40,440 --> 00:09:41,200
Right here?

123
00:09:41,550 --> 00:09:42,630
Yeah.

124
00:09:43,460 --> 00:09:44,990
He picked a good spot.

125
00:09:47,460 --> 00:09:52,540
[Beishan Village, Ma Deyong's Home]

126
00:10:55,500 --> 00:10:57,040
What are you looking for, Ming?

127
00:10:57,040 --> 00:10:57,920
Let me help you.

128
00:10:58,900 --> 00:11:00,030
Wait for me outside.

129
00:11:42,470 --> 00:11:43,680
What's wrong?

130
00:11:45,270 --> 00:11:47,090
Who's this girl, Ming?

131
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:54,770
Keep watch here.

132
00:12:07,230 --> 00:12:09,970
[Lover's Peak
in the suburb of Nanping City]

133
00:12:09,970 --> 00:12:12,110
I don't know where you were buried.

134
00:12:20,770 --> 00:12:21,960
Time flies.

135
00:12:25,210 --> 00:12:26,340
It's been ten years.

136
00:12:32,320 --> 00:12:35,190
If I didn't think
I'd see her when I got out,

137
00:12:36,140 --> 00:12:38,560
I would have died in prison.

138
00:12:56,430 --> 00:12:58,040
In prison,

139
00:12:59,840 --> 00:13:01,720
I figured a few things out.

140
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:02,980
Things to settle. Now.

141
00:13:05,590 --> 00:13:07,920
There are people who won't leave me alone.

142
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:09,800
I'm coming for them too.

143
00:13:11,790 --> 00:13:12,850
I'll drag them out.

144
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:15,790
We'll go down together.

145
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:24,280
Come in, Hua.

146
00:13:24,300 --> 00:13:25,290
Just put the things here.

147
00:13:25,290 --> 00:13:26,260
You can go back and rest.

148
00:13:26,260 --> 00:13:27,060
Okay, Mr. Hou.

149
00:13:27,650 --> 00:13:28,650
I'm home.

150
00:13:32,070 --> 00:13:32,760
Alright.

151
00:13:35,790 --> 00:13:37,910
I'm home!

152
00:13:38,910 --> 00:13:39,510
Daddy!

153
00:13:39,750 --> 00:13:40,500
Hey.

154
00:13:40,630 --> 00:13:41,860
My little pumpkin!

155
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:43,260
Did you miss Daddy?

156
00:13:43,550 --> 00:13:44,440
What are you looking for?

157
00:13:44,440 --> 00:13:46,560
What gift did you bring me this time?

158
00:13:46,670 --> 00:13:48,000
All you think about is gifts.

159
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:48,840
Come and see.

160
00:13:49,440 --> 00:13:50,480
See if you like it.

161
00:13:51,550 --> 00:13:52,080
Open it.

162
00:13:58,200 --> 00:13:59,000
Do you like it?

163
00:13:59,630 --> 00:14:00,440
I wanna go try it on!

164
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:01,270
Okay, try it on.

165
00:14:01,270 --> 00:14:01,800
Go ahead.

166
00:14:02,030 --> 00:14:02,670
Shanshan.

167
00:14:03,080 --> 00:14:05,080
Wash your hands first. Try it later.

168
00:14:06,360 --> 00:14:07,670
Wash your hands and eat first.

169
00:14:07,670 --> 00:14:09,270
Try it after dinner. Come on.

170
00:14:09,750 --> 00:14:10,550
Take this too.

171
00:14:11,160 --> 00:14:11,950
Hurry up.

172
00:14:14,840 --> 00:14:15,750
Come here, Xue.

173
00:14:15,750 --> 00:14:16,750
Take a look.

174
00:14:17,360 --> 00:14:19,090
Look what I got you — a necklace.

175
00:14:19,120 --> 00:14:19,790
Come on, try it on.

176
00:14:19,790 --> 00:14:21,050
I'm busy with the soup.

177
00:14:24,960 --> 00:14:26,030
Really, you.

178
00:14:26,030 --> 00:14:27,390
I've bought you so much jewelry,

179
00:14:27,390 --> 00:14:28,550
but you never wear any of it.

180
00:14:28,550 --> 00:14:29,960
You know me.

181
00:14:30,080 --> 00:14:32,080
I'm not interested in these things.

182
00:14:32,510 --> 00:14:34,270
Other husbands buy their wives things.

183
00:14:34,270 --> 00:14:35,960
You should have nice things too.

184
00:14:35,960 --> 00:14:36,720
Try it later.

185
00:14:37,150 --> 00:14:38,440
Just humor me.

186
00:14:40,720 --> 00:14:41,320
Shanshan.

187
00:14:42,560 --> 00:14:43,790
Did you wash your hands?

188
00:14:43,790 --> 00:14:44,550
Yes, I did.

189
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:45,960
Let's dig in.

190
00:14:53,670 --> 00:14:54,710
What a feast.

191
00:14:54,960 --> 00:14:57,220
I'll serve some soup for Mom first, okay?

192
00:14:57,480 --> 00:14:58,010
Okay.

193
00:14:58,480 --> 00:14:59,610
Here you are, Honey.

194
00:15:00,050 --> 00:15:01,660
Mom's been working so hard, hasn't she?

195
00:15:01,660 --> 00:15:03,150
Have some more meat.

196
00:15:04,240 --> 00:15:05,430
Have some more soup.

197
00:15:05,720 --> 00:15:06,840
Mom's been working so hard.

198
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:08,690
Let's get her the best piece!

199
00:15:08,810 --> 00:15:09,890
Okay?

200
00:15:10,840 --> 00:15:12,200
This piece is good.

201
00:15:12,200 --> 00:15:13,840
And some more soup.

202
00:15:14,960 --> 00:15:16,990
Have a piece. What is this called?

203
00:15:17,320 --> 00:15:18,440
Corn.

204
00:15:19,950 --> 00:15:20,500
Chang.

205
00:15:21,230 --> 00:15:22,310
Is he back?

206
00:15:22,440 --> 00:15:23,820
Not yet, Ming.

207
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:26,410
Keep an eye on it.

208
00:15:33,240 --> 00:15:34,440
Let's give it our all!

209
00:15:34,460 --> 00:15:34,750
Okay.

210
00:15:34,750 --> 00:15:35,240
Now,

211
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:37,080
let's start our first competition,

212
00:15:37,080 --> 00:15:38,080
the lightning round.

213
00:15:38,080 --> 00:15:39,870
First, we'll show you a video,

214
00:15:39,870 --> 00:15:41,150
showing the entire manufacturing process,

215
00:15:41,150 --> 00:15:43,870
from raw materials
to the finished product.

216
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:45,390
The first person to correctly identify

217
00:15:45,390 --> 00:15:49,030
what is being made during this process

218
00:15:49,030 --> 00:15:50,550
will be the winner.

219
00:15:50,550 --> 00:15:51,440
For instance,

220
00:15:51,440 --> 00:15:52,240
let's say

221
00:15:52,240 --> 00:15:54,550
we show you a video of making shoes.

222
00:15:54,790 --> 00:15:55,350
If...

223
00:15:55,790 --> 00:15:56,790
Good boy, Taotao.

224
00:15:59,140 --> 00:16:00,960
[Jinxiu Villa]

225
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:02,420
Be a good boy and stay here.

226
00:16:08,840 --> 00:16:09,320
Taotao!

227
00:16:09,920 --> 00:16:10,080
Taotao, don't run.

228
00:16:10,080 --> 00:16:11,070
[Jinxiu Villa]

229
00:16:12,720 --> 00:16:13,600
Taotao.

230
00:16:15,600 --> 00:16:16,920
Taotao, don't run.

231
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:18,570
Taotao, stay there.

232
00:16:20,200 --> 00:16:21,320
Stay, Taotao.

233
00:16:23,510 --> 00:16:24,150
Shanshan,

234
00:16:24,870 --> 00:16:26,930
come downstairs and have some fruit.

235
00:16:28,630 --> 00:16:29,440
Shanshan?

236
00:16:31,010 --> 00:16:32,450
Taotao, don't run.

237
00:16:33,080 --> 00:16:34,340
Taotao, stop running.

238
00:16:35,840 --> 00:16:36,960
Taotao.

239
00:16:36,980 --> 00:16:38,100
Taotao.

240
00:16:44,080 --> 00:16:44,550
What are you doing?

241
00:16:44,550 --> 00:16:45,350
Stop running.

242
00:16:47,200 --> 00:16:47,840
Hou Jun.

243
00:16:49,720 --> 00:16:51,250
Shanshan isn't in her room.

244
00:16:51,320 --> 00:16:52,050
Don't worry.

245
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:53,510
She's probably out walking the dog.

246
00:16:53,510 --> 00:16:55,330
But where would she go this late?

247
00:16:55,910 --> 00:16:56,320
Alright.

248
00:16:56,320 --> 00:16:57,840
Let's go out and look for her, okay?

249
00:16:57,840 --> 00:16:58,370
Let's go.

250
00:17:04,720 --> 00:17:06,099
Hey! You! Stop!

251
00:17:06,190 --> 00:17:07,990
Stop! Stop right there!

252
00:17:12,550 --> 00:17:13,510
It was 8:30 PM.

253
00:17:13,510 --> 00:17:15,440
We had to patrol the neighborhood.

254
00:17:15,640 --> 00:17:16,720
On our way back,

255
00:17:16,720 --> 00:17:18,390
I heard a dog barking.

256
00:17:18,589 --> 00:17:19,880
When I rushed over,

257
00:17:19,880 --> 00:17:20,829
I saw a man

258
00:17:20,829 --> 00:17:23,160
carrying off a little girl
and running away.

259
00:17:23,160 --> 00:17:24,109
I chased after him,

260
00:17:24,109 --> 00:17:25,069
but he was gone,

261
00:17:25,069 --> 00:17:27,030
so I called the police immediately.

262
00:17:27,030 --> 00:17:28,630
Did you see his face clearly?

263
00:17:29,960 --> 00:17:31,410
Is this your ball?

264
00:17:34,520 --> 00:17:36,270
Who tied you up here?

265
00:17:36,550 --> 00:17:37,110
Mr. Hou,

266
00:17:37,110 --> 00:17:37,830
recently,

267
00:17:38,030 --> 00:17:38,720
in your life

268
00:17:38,720 --> 00:17:39,400
or work,

269
00:17:39,400 --> 00:17:42,000
have you had conflicts with anyone?

270
00:17:42,350 --> 00:17:43,070
No.

271
00:17:43,640 --> 00:17:45,440
No conflicts in business, either?

272
00:17:45,440 --> 00:17:46,310
No.

273
00:17:46,830 --> 00:17:49,110
Have you received any threats,

274
00:17:49,110 --> 00:17:50,030
or any ransom demands?

275
00:17:50,030 --> 00:17:51,740
No, definitely not.

276
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:53,530
Everything is natural.

277
00:18:05,750 --> 00:18:08,240
Has anything unusual happened
at home recently?

278
00:18:08,240 --> 00:18:09,550
Officer.

279
00:18:10,920 --> 00:18:13,510
Let me go through it
with you again from the beginning.

280
00:18:13,510 --> 00:18:14,540
It's like this.

281
00:18:15,030 --> 00:18:17,200
I fell asleep after dinner today.

282
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:19,160
Then, our girl went upstairs
to do homework.

283
00:18:19,160 --> 00:18:20,720
Later, her mom got
a plate of fruit for her

284
00:18:20,720 --> 00:18:21,750
and called her downstairs to eat,

285
00:18:21,750 --> 00:18:23,920
but when she went upstairs,
she found she was gone.

286
00:18:23,920 --> 00:18:25,880
We figured she just ran out to play.

287
00:18:25,880 --> 00:18:27,920
You know how kids are
— they can be naughty.

288
00:18:27,920 --> 00:18:29,880
Then, when we came out,
we realized she was missing.

289
00:18:29,880 --> 00:18:30,510
Then we panicked

290
00:18:30,510 --> 00:18:31,750
and called the police.

291
00:18:31,750 --> 00:18:34,150
That's basically the situation right now.

292
00:18:34,590 --> 00:18:35,750
Mr. Hou, Mrs. Hou,

293
00:18:35,960 --> 00:18:37,440
we will do our best

294
00:18:37,440 --> 00:18:38,750
to help you find your child.

295
00:18:38,750 --> 00:18:40,720
If you remember anything,

296
00:18:40,720 --> 00:18:42,200
please notify us immediately.

297
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:43,330
We definitely will.

298
00:18:43,520 --> 00:18:45,580
We are really worried sick right now.

299
00:18:45,680 --> 00:18:46,640
No, no, no.

300
00:18:46,640 --> 00:18:47,240
Don't worry.

301
00:18:47,240 --> 00:18:48,240
Trust the police.

302
00:18:48,430 --> 00:18:50,890
They will definitely help us
find our child.

303
00:18:56,720 --> 00:18:57,860
Hello, Ming.

304
00:18:58,180 --> 00:18:58,860
Chang.

305
00:18:59,350 --> 00:19:00,470
Is Ma Derong back?

306
00:19:01,030 --> 00:19:02,340
No, Boss.

307
00:19:03,070 --> 00:19:04,640
Take all the photos back.

308
00:19:04,760 --> 00:19:05,810
Round up the crew

309
00:19:06,520 --> 00:19:07,830
and drop everything

310
00:19:08,120 --> 00:19:08,780
to find him!

311
00:19:09,470 --> 00:19:10,000
Alright.

312
00:19:11,560 --> 00:19:13,580
[Police]

313
00:19:13,670 --> 00:19:17,450
[Surveillance System]

314
00:19:20,280 --> 00:19:22,340
[Surveillance System]

315
00:19:24,590 --> 00:19:25,750
[June 5, 2010]

316
00:19:25,750 --> 00:19:26,910
Check that car.

317
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:28,200
Several cars just passed by.

318
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:29,630
Why only check this one?

319
00:19:29,960 --> 00:19:32,420
Have you ever seen a car
with such a dirty body

320
00:19:32,750 --> 00:19:34,480
but such a clean license plate?

321
00:19:35,070 --> 00:19:35,800
A fake plate?

322
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:37,880
Renyi,

323
00:19:37,880 --> 00:19:39,000
go to the Traffic Police

324
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:40,400
and ask for their assistance

325
00:19:40,400 --> 00:19:42,400
to investigate this silver Nissan.

326
00:19:42,510 --> 00:19:43,200
On it.

327
00:19:43,380 --> 00:19:46,590
[Rent at a Low Price]

328
00:19:46,660 --> 00:19:48,900
[Sancheng Financial Services]

329
00:19:55,640 --> 00:20:00,070
[Harmony Brings Prosperity]

330
00:20:00,070 --> 00:20:02,030
You're still looking at these photos?

331
00:20:02,030 --> 00:20:03,360
You stayed up all night?

332
00:20:03,750 --> 00:20:04,950
Eat something first.

333
00:20:05,020 --> 00:20:06,080
Take a look at this.

334
00:20:06,830 --> 00:20:07,560
What's that?

335
00:20:17,340 --> 00:20:18,530
I know this guy.

336
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:21,680
He's a gambler, Wang Bingkun.

337
00:20:21,700 --> 00:20:23,430
I've collected debts from him.

338
00:20:26,810 --> 00:20:28,530
He's in all three photos.

339
00:20:28,930 --> 00:20:30,330
Is it such a coincidence?

340
00:20:30,550 --> 00:20:31,880
It's not a coincidence.

341
00:20:32,750 --> 00:20:34,480
He's been following Shanshan.

342
00:20:35,520 --> 00:20:38,680
So it seems
Ma Derong didn't kidnap the girl.

343
00:20:39,350 --> 00:20:40,720
It was Wang Bingkun.

344
00:20:42,720 --> 00:20:45,000
Put the word out: find this guy.

345
00:20:45,310 --> 00:20:46,970
There's money in it if they do.

346
00:20:47,400 --> 00:20:49,200
Keep looking for Ma Derong, too.

347
00:20:51,080 --> 00:20:51,610
Got it.

348
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:53,500
I'll go right now.

349
00:21:25,270 --> 00:21:26,780
Go upstairs and rest a bit.

350
00:21:28,090 --> 00:21:30,020
I'll call you if anything happens.

351
00:21:30,680 --> 00:21:31,600
Okay?

352
00:21:35,480 --> 00:21:36,640
It's no use for us all to wait here.

353
00:21:36,640 --> 00:21:37,440
Go have a rest.

354
00:21:41,830 --> 00:21:43,520
Mr. and Mrs. Hou,

355
00:21:44,070 --> 00:21:46,000
you two should take turns resting.

356
00:21:46,160 --> 00:21:48,270
Okay? You need to keep your strength up.

357
00:21:48,270 --> 00:21:49,350
Situations like this

358
00:21:49,350 --> 00:21:51,790
where kidnappers
don't contact the family for days

359
00:21:51,790 --> 00:21:53,320
do happen from time to time.

360
00:21:53,350 --> 00:21:54,270
Cases like this

361
00:21:54,270 --> 00:21:55,440
just take a long time.

362
00:21:55,440 --> 00:21:56,400
So we'd better

363
00:21:56,400 --> 00:21:57,880
be prepared for the long haul.

364
00:21:57,880 --> 00:21:58,880
No matter what...

365
00:22:06,030 --> 00:22:06,830
Ming.

366
00:22:08,400 --> 00:22:08,800
Speak.

367
00:22:08,930 --> 00:22:11,390
Wang Bingkun
should be hiding in Hulu Alley.

368
00:22:11,880 --> 00:22:13,960
What do you mean by "should"? Be clear.

369
00:22:13,960 --> 00:22:14,830
He's right in Hulu Alley.

370
00:22:14,830 --> 00:22:16,890
Second floor, Building 17. I'm sure.

371
00:22:17,820 --> 00:22:18,400
Got it.

372
00:22:21,830 --> 00:22:22,960
I'm coming with you?

373
00:22:31,220 --> 00:22:31,980
Hello?

374
00:22:35,360 --> 00:22:36,470
Okay, I got it.

375
00:22:37,880 --> 00:22:38,750
Any news?

376
00:22:39,490 --> 00:22:41,860
We have some new leads.

377
00:22:41,890 --> 00:22:42,720
Don't worry.

378
00:22:42,740 --> 00:22:44,130
We'll find your girl as soon as possible.

379
00:22:44,130 --> 00:22:45,860
Our colleagues will stay here.

380
00:22:46,320 --> 00:22:47,120
You go with me.

381
00:22:47,810 --> 00:22:48,840
We appreciate your hard work.

382
00:22:48,840 --> 00:22:49,840
Don't mention it.

383
00:22:55,160 --> 00:22:56,200
It will be fine.

384
00:23:59,490 --> 00:23:59,960
Eat it.

385
00:24:02,390 --> 00:24:08,090
[Block 2, No. 21 Hulu Alley]

386
00:24:20,310 --> 00:24:20,960
Who is it?

387
00:24:22,750 --> 00:24:23,510
Who is it?

388
00:24:27,170 --> 00:24:29,130
[Police]

389
00:24:29,180 --> 00:24:31,510
[Police]

390
00:24:33,160 --> 00:24:33,720
Who?

391
00:25:16,030 --> 00:25:17,090
Seal off the scene.

392
00:25:17,360 --> 00:25:18,960
Pull all nearby surveillance footage.

393
00:25:18,960 --> 00:25:20,160
-Yes, Sir.
-Yes, Sir.

394
00:25:57,190 --> 00:25:58,270
[Police]

395
00:25:58,270 --> 00:25:59,400
You know,

396
00:25:59,400 --> 00:26:00,880
when I transferred
from the factory Security Department

397
00:26:00,880 --> 00:26:02,030
back then,

398
00:26:02,030 --> 00:26:03,830
this building wasn't even here.

399
00:26:04,590 --> 00:26:06,270
This is the Equipment Room.

400
00:26:06,270 --> 00:26:07,550
This is our Second Squad.

401
00:26:07,550 --> 00:26:08,270
Chief Liu.

402
00:26:08,270 --> 00:26:09,750
Everyone, may I have your attention?

403
00:26:09,750 --> 00:26:11,160
Let me introduce him to you.

404
00:26:11,160 --> 00:26:12,110
Wu Yunpeng,

405
00:26:12,270 --> 00:26:13,880
a top graduate from the police academy,

406
00:26:13,880 --> 00:26:16,110
is joining the Second Squad today.

407
00:26:17,310 --> 00:26:18,960
Hello everyone, I'm Wu Yunpeng.

408
00:26:18,960 --> 00:26:20,710
Honored to join the Second Squad.

409
00:26:20,710 --> 00:26:21,640
I'm flattered.

410
00:26:21,750 --> 00:26:22,550
You're all my seniors.

411
00:26:22,550 --> 00:26:24,550
I look forward to learning from you.

412
00:26:24,550 --> 00:26:25,520
Hi, Superstar.

413
00:26:25,880 --> 00:26:27,280
Show us your pretty face.

414
00:26:27,980 --> 00:26:28,640
Hi, Mom Liu.

415
00:26:28,960 --> 00:26:29,640
She's Captain Qin.

416
00:26:29,640 --> 00:26:31,240
I believe you've heard about

417
00:26:31,270 --> 00:26:33,030
all the major cases in our bureau,

418
00:26:33,030 --> 00:26:34,960
especially
the famous July 18th shooting case...

419
00:26:34,960 --> 00:26:35,550
Mom Liu,

420
00:26:36,310 --> 00:26:37,170
that's enough.

421
00:26:37,400 --> 00:26:39,600
I've heard a lot about you, Captain Qin.

422
00:26:40,920 --> 00:26:41,980
Let's welcome him.

423
00:26:43,440 --> 00:26:44,110
Welcome.

424
00:26:47,230 --> 00:26:48,860
Let me also update you...

425
00:26:49,530 --> 00:26:50,450
This desk...

426
00:26:50,590 --> 00:26:52,440
won't be available anytime soon.

427
00:26:52,440 --> 00:26:53,370
You can sit here.

428
00:26:53,980 --> 00:26:54,350
Okay.

429
00:26:54,350 --> 00:26:55,640
It's fine.

430
00:26:56,660 --> 00:26:57,920
Yes, this spot is good.

431
00:26:57,940 --> 00:26:59,070
Close to Captain Qin.

432
00:26:59,070 --> 00:26:59,440
Yes.

433
00:26:59,440 --> 00:26:59,970
Alright.

434
00:27:00,270 --> 00:27:01,400
If you need anything, just tell me.

435
00:27:01,400 --> 00:27:02,400
Alright, Mom Liu.

436
00:27:02,680 --> 00:27:03,830
Arrangements are made. Go back.

437
00:27:03,830 --> 00:27:04,640
Okay.

438
00:27:05,720 --> 00:27:06,400
See you, Chief Liu.

439
00:27:06,400 --> 00:27:07,070
I'm off.

440
00:27:09,590 --> 00:27:10,440
What's your name again?

441
00:27:10,440 --> 00:27:11,160
Wu Yunpeng.

442
00:27:12,240 --> 00:27:13,900
Alright. You're here to work.

443
00:27:14,110 --> 00:27:14,800
Prepare for the meeting.

444
00:27:14,800 --> 00:27:15,800
Yes, Captain Qin.

445
00:27:16,680 --> 00:27:16,720
On the night of June 5,

446
00:27:16,720 --> 00:27:17,790
[Hou Shanshan] [Wang Bingkun]
[Father, Hou Jun] [Mother, Xia Xue]

447
00:27:17,790 --> 00:27:20,000
a security at Jinxiu Villa
reported a case.

448
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:21,960
A girl living in the villa area

449
00:27:21,960 --> 00:27:23,510
was suspected of being
kidnapped at her doorstep.

450
00:27:23,510 --> 00:27:24,160
[The Kidnapping Case of Hou Shanshan]

451
00:27:24,160 --> 00:27:26,880
The girl is identified as Hou Shanshan,
aged ten.

452
00:27:26,880 --> 00:27:28,640
She is the only daughter
of a famous local entrepreneur,

453
00:27:28,640 --> 00:27:31,110
Hou Jun, Chairman of Jinwan Maritime.

454
00:27:31,680 --> 00:27:33,640
Since the couple, Hou Jun and Xia Xue,
insisted

455
00:27:33,640 --> 00:27:35,310
that they hadn't offended anyone,

456
00:27:35,310 --> 00:27:36,920
we initially suspected

457
00:27:36,920 --> 00:27:39,110
it was a kidnapping for ransom.

458
00:27:39,400 --> 00:27:40,640
But so far,

459
00:27:40,680 --> 00:27:43,540
we haven't received any calls
from the kidnappers.

460
00:27:44,700 --> 00:27:45,700
I have a question.

461
00:27:46,440 --> 00:27:47,720
As for Hou Jun,

462
00:27:48,030 --> 00:27:49,960
even if he has no personal enemies,

463
00:27:50,110 --> 00:27:52,110
doesn't he have rivals in business?

464
00:27:52,240 --> 00:27:53,000
How could he be so sure

465
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:54,800
that he hadn't offended anyone?

466
00:27:55,660 --> 00:27:56,370
Go on.

467
00:27:57,800 --> 00:27:59,910
Although clues were limited,

468
00:28:00,110 --> 00:28:00,780
with the cooperation

469
00:28:00,780 --> 00:28:01,440
[The suspect
in the murder of Wang Bingkun]

470
00:28:01,440 --> 00:28:01,630
and the assistance of the traffic police,

471
00:28:01,630 --> 00:28:02,680
[Missing on June 5]

472
00:28:02,680 --> 00:28:02,930
we quickly identified this cloned

473
00:28:02,930 --> 00:28:04,310
[June 5, 2010]

474
00:28:04,310 --> 00:28:05,400
silver Nissan,

475
00:28:05,640 --> 00:28:07,550
and tracked down the suspect.

476
00:28:08,110 --> 00:28:10,390
But when we arrived at the hideout,

477
00:28:10,440 --> 00:28:12,640
we found the suspect had been murdered.

478
00:28:14,880 --> 00:28:16,280
His name is Wang Bingkun,

479
00:28:16,310 --> 00:28:18,090
32 years old, unemployed.

480
00:28:18,240 --> 00:28:19,330
He came from Shuanghe City

481
00:28:19,330 --> 00:28:20,680
and had no relatives in Nanping.

482
00:28:20,680 --> 00:28:22,880
His social connections
are still being investigated.

483
00:28:22,880 --> 00:28:25,830
However, items left at the scene indicate

484
00:28:25,880 --> 00:28:26,640
that Hou Shanshan

485
00:28:26,640 --> 00:28:29,440
was indeed present
at the kidnapper's hideout.

486
00:28:31,560 --> 00:28:33,230
But clues remain scarce.

487
00:28:33,400 --> 00:28:35,310
Under Wang Bingkun's fingernails,

488
00:28:35,310 --> 00:28:37,040
we found human tissue residue.

489
00:28:37,200 --> 00:28:40,110
It's suspected to be from
a struggle with the killer.

490
00:28:40,110 --> 00:28:41,810
Also, the surveillance camera captured

491
00:28:41,810 --> 00:28:42,880
[June 7, 2010]

492
00:28:42,880 --> 00:28:44,810
the suspected killer from behind.

493
00:28:48,880 --> 00:28:49,640
Alright.

494
00:28:50,110 --> 00:28:52,080
I'm going to visit the child's parents.

495
00:28:52,080 --> 00:28:52,750
Captain Qin,

496
00:28:52,750 --> 00:28:53,880
I want to go with you.

497
00:28:55,960 --> 00:28:57,020
Wu Yunpeng, right?

498
00:28:58,830 --> 00:29:00,020
Go learn the ropes.

499
00:29:00,940 --> 00:29:01,580
Thanks.

500
00:29:01,770 --> 00:29:02,650
Take them all.

501
00:29:04,310 --> 00:29:05,110
You're with Captain Qin now.

502
00:29:05,110 --> 00:29:06,710
Say goodbye to lunch breaks!

503
00:29:25,680 --> 00:29:30,510
[Jinxiu Villa]

504
00:29:30,510 --> 00:29:31,240
Captain Qin.

505
00:29:35,110 --> 00:29:36,710
Since the kidnapper is dead,

506
00:29:36,750 --> 00:29:38,010
where is the child now?

507
00:29:39,030 --> 00:29:40,030
So we suspect

508
00:29:40,030 --> 00:29:42,440
this isn't a simple kidnapping case,

509
00:29:42,460 --> 00:29:44,260
and it's not just about money.

510
00:29:44,720 --> 00:29:45,440
Mr. Hou,

511
00:29:45,720 --> 00:29:48,250
think about
whether you've offended anyone.

512
00:29:49,590 --> 00:29:50,720
I'm a businessman.

513
00:29:50,980 --> 00:29:52,270
Competition in business

514
00:29:52,270 --> 00:29:52,960
is natural.

515
00:29:53,310 --> 00:29:55,510
Besides, we're all legitimate businessmen.

516
00:29:55,510 --> 00:29:56,920
It's unnecessary to get involved
in kidnapping

517
00:29:56,920 --> 00:29:58,400
or murder.

518
00:30:00,410 --> 00:30:01,810
What about you, Mrs. Hou?

519
00:30:05,240 --> 00:30:07,440
We did some background checks.

520
00:30:07,920 --> 00:30:10,590
Shanshan's birthday is May 2000.

521
00:30:10,960 --> 00:30:12,310
But you registered your marriage

522
00:30:12,310 --> 00:30:14,400
was in April 2003.

523
00:30:14,830 --> 00:30:15,690
I'd like to ask,

524
00:30:16,110 --> 00:30:18,640
why was there such a long gap?

525
00:30:19,350 --> 00:30:20,810
Could you please explain?

526
00:30:24,160 --> 00:30:25,200
Well,

527
00:30:27,330 --> 00:30:29,530
I'm not Shanshan's biological father.

528
00:30:31,090 --> 00:30:32,240
When Xia Xue married me,

529
00:30:32,240 --> 00:30:33,970
she brought Shanshan with her.

530
00:30:34,880 --> 00:30:36,740
The child was already 3 years old.

531
00:30:39,830 --> 00:30:41,760
Then who is the biological father?

532
00:30:43,050 --> 00:30:45,030
That's my wife's private business.

533
00:30:45,030 --> 00:30:45,510
Besides,

534
00:30:45,510 --> 00:30:47,770
it has nothing to do with the case, right?

535
00:30:47,810 --> 00:30:48,400
With the time you have,

536
00:30:48,400 --> 00:30:49,350
why don't you

537
00:30:49,350 --> 00:30:50,440
go look for her

538
00:30:50,440 --> 00:30:51,400
and find out who took her?

539
00:30:51,400 --> 00:30:52,240
Can you, please?

540
00:30:52,240 --> 00:30:52,880
Mr. Hou,

541
00:30:53,030 --> 00:30:54,550
we have deployed a large police force

542
00:30:54,550 --> 00:30:55,240
to find the child.

543
00:30:55,240 --> 00:30:56,830
Then what are you doing here?

544
00:30:56,830 --> 00:30:58,880
Everyone investigates cases differently.

545
00:30:58,880 --> 00:30:59,960
Only by understanding

546
00:30:59,960 --> 00:31:01,400
everything about Shanshan

547
00:31:01,400 --> 00:31:03,960
can I find her sooner.

548
00:31:08,720 --> 00:31:09,880
Sorry. Sorry.

549
00:31:13,110 --> 00:31:13,680
Wu.

550
00:31:17,490 --> 00:31:17,720
[June 7, 2010]

551
00:31:17,720 --> 00:31:18,850
Do you know this man?

552
00:31:25,960 --> 00:31:26,020
This is surveillance
from the neighborhood

553
00:31:26,020 --> 00:31:27,240
[June 7, 2010]

554
00:31:27,240 --> 00:31:28,570
where Wang Bingkun hid.

555
00:31:31,310 --> 00:31:33,370
This person was present at the scene.

556
00:31:33,720 --> 00:31:34,590
We highly suspect

557
00:31:34,590 --> 00:31:35,740
he killed Wang Bingkun

558
00:31:35,740 --> 00:31:36,800
and took the child.

559
00:31:37,080 --> 00:31:37,590
[June 7, 2010]

560
00:31:37,590 --> 00:31:38,790
It's just a back view.

561
00:31:39,460 --> 00:31:41,060
We can't make an ID from that.

562
00:31:45,030 --> 00:31:45,920
Mrs. Hou,

563
00:31:46,510 --> 00:31:47,900
take a closer look.

564
00:31:48,390 --> 00:31:49,250
Do you know him?

565
00:31:49,290 --> 00:31:50,620
[June 7, 2010]

566
00:32:00,880 --> 00:32:01,510
No.

567
00:32:06,110 --> 00:32:07,570
I need to use the bathroom.

568
00:32:17,990 --> 00:32:18,640
You two...

569
00:32:20,410 --> 00:32:21,640
You don't suspect my wife
has some involvement,

570
00:32:21,640 --> 00:32:23,160
do you?

571
00:32:23,880 --> 00:32:26,010
We're just asking routine questions.

572
00:32:26,260 --> 00:32:27,430
I just hope

573
00:32:27,720 --> 00:32:29,830
you can help us find our child soon.

574
00:32:30,950 --> 00:32:31,980
We'll do our best.

575
00:32:32,350 --> 00:32:34,790
Please notify us if you go out.

576
00:32:44,160 --> 00:32:44,890
Captain Qin,

577
00:32:45,510 --> 00:32:47,510
does the child's background matter?

578
00:32:47,510 --> 00:32:48,880
Are we going off track?

579
00:32:49,790 --> 00:32:51,880
My car had a flat tire a while ago.

580
00:32:51,880 --> 00:32:53,500
So I took it for repairs.

581
00:32:53,790 --> 00:32:55,030
The mechanic checked it,

582
00:32:55,030 --> 00:32:56,000
but he found nothing wrong.

583
00:32:56,000 --> 00:32:57,660
So he just replaced one for me.

584
00:32:58,830 --> 00:32:59,890
I hadn't driven far

585
00:33:01,790 --> 00:33:02,180
before it blew out again.

586
00:33:02,180 --> 00:33:04,440
[Jinxiu Villa]

587
00:33:04,440 --> 00:33:05,160
And then?

588
00:33:05,830 --> 00:33:06,350
[Jinxiu Villa]

589
00:33:06,350 --> 00:33:07,810
I took it to the repair shop

590
00:33:08,080 --> 00:33:09,440
for a thorough check.

591
00:33:10,200 --> 00:33:11,030
The mechanic told me

592
00:33:11,030 --> 00:33:13,030
that my shock absorbers were too soft.

593
00:33:13,030 --> 00:33:14,720
Whenever someone sat in the back seats,

594
00:33:14,720 --> 00:33:16,550
the chassis would rub against the tires,

595
00:33:16,550 --> 00:33:17,790
causing a tire blowout.

596
00:33:17,790 --> 00:33:19,320
It's the same with our case.

597
00:33:19,790 --> 00:33:21,880
We need to check the superficial stuff,

598
00:33:21,880 --> 00:33:24,510
but we've also got to
nail down the root cause.

599
00:33:28,250 --> 00:33:31,790
[Police]

600
